and,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isabelle","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabel Mering was born in 1345. She had at least 1 son with Henry I Fenton."},"et":{"1345–":"1345–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","1345":"1345","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","Fenton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Fenton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fi":{"1345–":"1345–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1345–Female":"1345–Kuollut","1345":"1345","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","Fenton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Fenton, Nottinghamshire, England"},"fr":{"1345–":"1345–Décédée","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1370–Male":"1370–Décédé","1345–Female":"1345–Décédée","1345":"1345","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","Fenton, Nottinghamshire, England":"Fenton, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Isabel Mering est née en 1345. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Henry I Fenton."},"de":{"1345–":"1345–Verstorben","1340–Male":"1340–Verstorben","1370–Male":"1370–Verstorben","1345–Female":"1345–Verstorben","1345":"1345","1340":"1340","1370":"1370","Fenton, Nottin